elements.description:
`app-drawer-morph-element`
A navigation drawer that can slide in from the left or right and that morphs for current mobile OS

properties.name: opened
properties.description: The opened state of the drawer.

properties.name: persistent
properties.description: The drawer does not have a scrim and cannot be swiped close.

properties.name: transitionDuration
properties.description: The transition duration of the drawer in milliseconds.

properties.name: align
properties.description:
The alignment of the drawer on the screen ('left', 'right', 'start' or 'end').
'start' computes to left and 'end' to right in LTR layout and vice versa in RTL
layout.

properties.name: position
properties.description: The computed, read-only position of the drawer on the screen ('left' or 'right').

properties.name: swipeOpen
properties.description: Create an area at the edge of the screen to swipe open the drawer.

properties.name: noFocusTrap
properties.description: Trap keyboard focus when the drawer is opened and not persistent.

properties.name: disableSwipe
properties.description: Disables swiping on the drawer.

properties.name: platform
properties.description: Detects the platform if it is either  - 'ios', 'android' or 'windows-phone' or if none of the 3 were identified returns 'unkown'

methods.name: toggle
methods.description: Toggles the drawer open and close.

methods.name: getWidth
methods.description: Gets the width of the drawer.

return.desc: The width of the drawer in pixels.

`morph-pages`
Pages element that morphs for current mobile OS

properties.name: threshold
properties.description: Value used to decide if page get swipe or not

properties.name: transitionTimingFunction
properties.description: The CSS transition timing function applied.

properties.name: navigationHistory
properties.description: Array of previous pages location hash or value

properties.name: pageChangeAnimationDirection
properties.description: Page animation direction setter that links wiht morph-location's last-navigation-direction

methods.name: animationEnd
methods.description: Used by android-animation.js and ios-animation.js to remove styles on current and previous pages

methods.name: _handleTrackSwipe
methods.description: This method is called when event 'track' is fired. This event listener is set up in constructor

methods.name: _onIronSelectItem
methods.description: Listens to 'iron-select' and calls animation unless not needed

methods.name: _onIronDeselectItem
methods.description: deselectItem listening to 'iron-deselect' event. Fires everytime selected is deselected
